The main contributions are:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \emph{Fisher-guided federated communication control.} We formulate token-level Fisher sensitivity as a communication control primitive for federated LLM fine-tuning, enabling mixed-precision transmission that preserves semantically decisive evidence under severe uplink constraints.
    \item \emph{System-level gains under heterogeneity.} We demonstrate substantial reductions in cumulative uplink traffic (46$\times$) and straggler-limited time-to-accuracy (52\%) under realistic Non-IID client distributions and heterogeneous mobile uplinks.
    \item \emph{Edge deployability and dual-use benefits.} We validate feasibility on real edge hardware (NVIDIA Jetson), showing that Fisher estimation overhead is amortized by communication savings and that learned masks benefit both training communication and inference efficiency.
\end{itemize}

